This course introduces the structure of Estonian through its phonetics and phonology, morphology, syntax and semantics. Students are given an introduction to the basic concepts and terminology used in these branches of linguistics, and they gain understanding and experience in applying these concepts through analysis of Estonian.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to give an introduction to the basic characteristics of Estonian and the basic concepts used in linguistics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students completing this course will:
a. be familiar with key issues and approaches to investigating Estonian pronunciation, morphology and syntax and will be able to apply this knowledge in practice;
b. be competent in basic terminology used in linguistic analysis; and 
c. be able to analyse the structure of Estonian words and sentence in texts.
